<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910603-0103</DOCNO><DOCID>910603-0103.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Iran's Friendlier Face   Masks Same Old Terror</HL><DATE>06/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><RE>IRAN (IR)MIDDLE EAST (ML)</RE><LP>   I am writing in response to your April 29 page-one articleabout the situation in my home country, Iran. There aretragic and discouraging reports from millions of Iranians whohave left Iran because of economic disaster, and the fiercerepression of women, religious minorities and opponents. Inone week, recently, more than 800 women were arrested byorder of President Rafsanjani for not complying with theIslamic dress code. Massive executions for other crimescontinue; Amnesty International recorded more than 600 in1990.   The image of moderation by Khomeini's trained successor,President Rafsanjani, does not mean there will be any changein the nature of this regime. The fundamentalist rulers arestill trying to export their Islamic revolution, andterrorism.</LP><TEXT>   Mori Hosseini   Lenexa, Kan.</TEXT></DOC>